<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Maur: It would be nice to see your speed (and, if you're a posessor, your number of limbs/item slots) on the 'C'haracter screen and in the character dump. <p>
<strong><a href="./ZizzoTheInfinite">ZizzoTheInfinite</a>:</strong> I've put up <a class="external" href="./www.killerbunnies.org/angband/tome-showspd.diff"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">a patch</a> to add player speed to the character dump.  As for equipment slots, I think the equipment list already shows all (and only) the slots that are available in your current form. 
</p>
<h2 id="head-a192084c52f36bcb09cfa1c37e6b3ac169054bf7"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Resistance display for non-*ID*'ed objects</h2>
<p>
Kalirion: Vanilla already has this, and I think it would make a good addition to ToME.  The standard resists and abilities granted by ego and other non-artifact items should show up in the item description and on the resistance screen even if the items have not been *Identified*.  The random high resists, of course, should not.  Everyone already knows what the resists are, but its a pain having to figure out what resistance holes you have.  Or maybe this could be a ToME only option on the configuration screen. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./ZizzoTheInfinite">ZizzoTheInfinite</a></strong>:  Actually, the game already does that to an extent.  The lines in <tt>src/{a,e,k}_info.txt</tt> beginning with <tt>f:</tt> are "obvious" flags, that should show up on the grid or in the item descriptions without *ID*'ing the items.  Of course, the game's ideas about which flags should be obvious for which items may differ from yours... <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile2.png" alt="B)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
Kalirion:  Cool, thanks!  I guess I'll just go through the ego and item info files and change some of those to the 'f:' line <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: You need to add the flags to the 'f:' line, don't remove them from the 'F:' line. 
</p>
